value.title: Biden election: Mike Pence 'welcomes' senators' bid to derail result
value.excerpt: President Mike Pence has welcomed an effort by a group of senators to refuse to certify Joe Biden's presidential election win. The 11 Republican senators and senators-elect, led by Ted Cruz, want a 10-day delay to audit unsubstantiated allegations of election fraud.

value.title: Analysis: Republican efforts to undermine Biden victory expose growing anti-democratic streak
value.excerpt: The scattershot efforts to overturn President-elect Joe Biden's election victory are coalescing into a movement led by top Republicans determined to exploit a manufactured crisis for broader political gains.

value.title: Pence 'welcomes' congressional Republicans' bid to challenge electoral votes
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Saturday signaled his support for a bid by Republicans lawmakers to challenge electoral votes when Congress is expected to certify President-elect Joe Biden's victory in a meeting this week.
